    "Structured transactions: Structured transactions involve breaking down large transactions into smaller ones, typically over a period of time.",
    "This makes it difficult for authorities to detect that all the transactions are related to the same source. 6.",
    "Money launderers use complex networks: Money launderers will often use complex networks of intermediaries and offshore companies to transfer funds.",
    "This will make it even more difficult for authorities to trace the funds back to their original source. 7.",
    "Utilize front companies: Front companies are companies which are used to hide the real ownership of an individual or company."
